This falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also employs results from Graph and Information Theory, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the possible application of Shellsort in merging chains, which falls under the sub-category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the analysis of finding the true order by further pairwise comparisons suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
